fields.name: CCACH
fields.about: The Council of Canadians of African and Caribbean Heritage (CCACH) exists to undertake and support activities to enhance the social, economic and educational life of the African and Caribbean heritage communities.

fields.name: Canadian Soccer League
fields.about:
The Canadian Soccer League (CSL) is long-standing and is one of two professional soccer leagues in Canada. It is a continuation of earlier forerunner leagues, the National Soccer League (NSL), the Canadian National Soccer League (CNSL) and the Canadian Professional Soccer League (CPSL), going back more than 80 years.

The Canadian Premier League is the most recent entry into professional soccer in Canada with seven teams that kicked off its inaugural season on April 27, 2019.

Professional soccer in Canada also consists of three clubs in membership with Major League Soccer (MLS), the top tier league of 24 teams founded in 1993 and based in the United States. The Canadian clubs are Montreal Impact, Toronto FC and the Vancouver Whitecaps.

fields.name: Blab and Bake
fields.about:
Talk and Bake is a 100% volunteer-run non-profit organization located in Edmonton, Alberta, that recognizes that food is not only a nutritious substance, but it also connects us with each other, ourselves, and the world around us. 

Our aim is to create social spaces for participants to get to know each through creating meals and dining together. We are a non-partisan organization and our programming is open to all no matter identity or skill level.

Recognizing that food is a gateway to building bridges in our community, we started ‘Talk and Bake’ to help alleviate barriers people have to finding culturally relevant and nutritious foods. Some of our programming includes running grocery busses, cooking socials, developing community cookbooks resources on food safety and preparation.

fields.name: Edmonton Immigrant Services
fields.about: Edmonton Immigrant Services Association (EISA) was established by five individuals on December 16, 1976, under the Societies Act as a non-profit society. EISA is a direct result of an awareness that immigrants and refugees to Edmonton and the area did not meet all their needs. EISA’s founders recognized the newcomers’ unexpected life realities significantly affected their lives and their integration into Canadian society. The services were to be provided to immigrants and refugees in Edmonton and the area, regardless of age, gender, religion, nationality, or ethnic origin.

fields.name: Mechanical Turk Technologies
fields.about: Mechanical Turk (MTurk) is a crowdsourcing marketplace that makes it easier for individuals and businesses to outsource their processes and jobs to a distributed workforce who can perform these tasks virtually. This could include anything from conducting simple data validation and research to more subjective tasks like survey participation, content moderation, and more. MTurk enables companies to harness the collective intelligence, skills, and insights from a global workforce to streamline business processes, augment data collection and analysis, and accelerate machine learning development.

fields.name: Team Illuminator
fields.summary:
With the Team Illuminator, users can:

1. Take a self-assessment and determine their preferences for interacting with others at work.
2. Increase empathy, understand what drives people’s workplace values and behaviors.
3. Compare their values to teammates, and determine optimal collaboration strategies

Provides practical tips to apply the learning to a user’s teams. We can also train an HR business partner or coach a leader to facilitate a team discussion. Our excellent facilitators can run a team session for you and coach the leader and/or team members individually as needed.We also provide virtual and face to face training programs based on our assessment model.
